name: Classification Report
text: The graph below compares various model performance metrics.

name: Prediction Probability Chart
text: X-axis represents Index of datapoints present in the dataset. on Y-axis prediction probability is plotted.

name: PDP-ICE
text: Partial dependence plots (PDP) and Individual conditional expectation (ICE) plots can be used to visualize and analyze interaction between the target response and a set of input features of interest.

name: Precision-Recall Curve
text: A Precision-recall curve ( or PR Curve) is a plot of the precision (y-axis) and the recall (x-axis) for different probability thresholds.

name: Multiclass Precision-Recall Curve
text: Precision-Recall Curve for each class separately.

name: ROC Curve
text: ROC curve (Receiver Operating Characteristic curve) is a graph showing the performance of a classification model at all classification thresholds.

name: Multiclass ROC Curve
text: ROC curve for each class separately.

name: TPR, FPR At Every Threshold
text: X-axis represents threshold, Y-axis represents TPR and FPR
